---
title: Pasta alla Norma
source: Marcella Hazan
servings: 4
tags:
  - italian
  - pasta
  - eggplant
  - sicilian
---

Cut @eggplant{1%lb}(globe, 1-inch cubes) and toss with @salt{1%tsp}. Place in
a #colander{} and let drain for ~drain{30%minutes}. Pat dry with paper towels.

Heat @olive oil{1/4%cup} in a #large skillet{} over medium-high heat. Fry the
eggplant in batches for ~{4-5%minutes} per batch until golden on all sides.
Transfer to a #plate{} lined with paper towels.

In the same skillet, add @garlic{3%cloves}(sliced) and @red pepper flakes{1/4%tsp}.
Cook for ~{30%seconds}.

Add @canned San Marzano tomatoes{28%oz}(crushed by hand) and @fresh basil{6}(leaves, torn).
Simmer for ~{20%minutes} until thickened.

Meanwhile, bring a #large pot{} of salted water to a boil. Cook @rigatoni{1%lb}
until al dente according to package directions. Reserve @pasta water{1/2%cup}
before draining.

Toss the pasta with the tomato sauce, adding pasta water as needed. Fold in
the fried eggplant.

Serve topped with @ricotta salata{1/2%cup}(grated) and more torn @basil{}.
